== Open questions ==
Other than the problems with the extensions of tetration, there are several open questions concerning tetration, particularly when concerning the relations between number systems such as integers and irrational numbers:
* It is not known whether there is an integer formula_148 for which is an integer, because we could not calculate precisely enough the numbers of digits after the decimal points of formula_149. It is similar for for formula_150, as we are not aware of any other methods besides some direct computation. In fact, since formula_151, then formula_152. Given formula_153 and formula_154, then formula_155 for formula_150. It is believed that is not an integer for any positive integer , due to the algebraic independence of formula_157, given Schanuel&#x27;s conjecture.
* It is not known whether is rational for any positive integer and positive non-integer rational . For example, it is not known whether the positive root of the equation is a rational number.
* It is not known whether or (defined using Kneser&#x27;s extension) are rationals or not.

